  <datafield tag="545" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Founded in 1925 as the Michigan Association of Speech Teachers by twenty-nine speech teachers from around the state. The organization was formed to provide a forum for the exchange of ideas and establishment of standards related to speech communication pedagogy. The most significant achievements of the association include publication of curriculum guides and a scholarly journal, organization of annual state-wide professional conferences, setting of speech teacher certification standards, and</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="545" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">establishment of a job placement program. The organization changed its name to the Michigan Speech Association in 1950, and adopted its current name in 1983.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Comprised of documentation generated by the functions of members of the Executive Committee. The majority of the records are in the form of minutes, financial reports, budgets, topical files on association activities, committee reports, conference journals, and membership directories published by the association.</subfield>
  </datafield>
